OL,3,CHospitals Trust plan #160 million
OL,4,Cworth of cuts to plug budget gap
OL,6,F"We are currently facing financial
OL,7,Fchallenges and have produced a
OL,8,Fcomprehensive financial plan to reduce
OL,9,Four deficit and achieve a breakeven
OL,10,Fposition by April 2026.J"Our financial
OL,11,Fplan aims to support us in making
OL,12,Fsignificant savings over the coming
OL,13,Fyears but will do so in a way that
OL,14,Fdoes not compromise patient safety.
OL,15,F"We know there is more work to do,
OL,16,Fespecially to reduce our pay bill and
OL,17,Fwe cannot rule out a reduction in
OL,18,Fposts in the future. We know this will
OL,19,Fbe unsettling and want to make it
OL,20,Fclear that in these circumstances our
OL,21,Fpriority is to protect jobs and avoid
OL,22,Fcompulsory redundancies."JHe told a
OL,23,Fmeeting of the Trust's board on
OL,24,FThursday (May 9) that the cost-cutting
OL,25,Ftargets were "very ambitious" but he
OL,26,Fwas confident they could be met.
